parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause loss of control, accidents, and leave the driver stranded.
Muffler/exhaust system failure can cause damage to surrounding components, affect engine performance, and lead to accidents.
symptoms: pieces of rusted muffler debris stop exhaust flow
and back pressure builds up against the PFE sensor and engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clamps and mounts failure can cause engine damage, affect engine performance, and lead to accidents.
symptoms: Clamps holding muffler in place break
and engine torque breaks seal on air filter.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: the engine check light illuminates on the dash
the vehicle cuts off without prior warning
the ignition lock does not work properly
the key sticks in the ignition lock
the vehicle stalls when coming to a stop
the vehicle stalls while traveling at high speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: the wires coming from the car to the alternator melt
the cable entering the alternator melts and bubbles
a high-pitched whiney sound is heard
flames come from under the hood.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: electrical problems cause failure of wiring harness/spark module/main computer/ground wires
the wiring harness to blower motor melts/burns
the control head assembly to harness fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake adjuster can cause the wheels to lock up, leading to loss of control, skidding, and accidents.
symptoms: brake pedal goes to the floor

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, leading to loss of braking ability, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Brake pedal goes to the floor

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake spring can cause loud noise, brake failure, and loss of control, leading to accidents.
Brake fade can cause the brakes to fail, leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
Improper repair and maintenance can cause brake failure, leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
